cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.MM

This paper deals with the analysis of a mobile ad hoc network powered by energy harvesting, which involves the study of wireless communication, network optimization, and stochastic modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the optimization of transmission power, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of stochastic-geometry models and random-walk theory suggests the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves the use of mathematical tools such as polynomial equations, which suggests the category of cs.MA (Mathematical Software). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of wireless networks, which suggests the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
